    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\n```cython\nraise TypeError(f\"{name} didn't expect {a_or_the} Spanish Inquisition !\")\n```\nThis currently generates verbose f-string formatting code for something that's almost always an edge case.\nOther formatting ways like `%`-formatting are similarly affected (and mostly get turned into f-strings).\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nWe should try to translate the above into `PyErr_Format()` calls when we detect that a builtin exception is being constructed and raised. They are much simpler and use a lot less code. Performance is almost never an issue here.\n\nNote that this must exclude arbitrary function calls like `raise build_exception(how, why, \"…\")`, thus the restriction on known builtins.\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
